<p><b>Social Cognitive Theory</b>, used in psychology, education, and communication, posits that portions of an individual's knowledge acquisition can be directly related to <a href="/wiki/Observation" title="Observation">observing</a> others within the context of social interactions, experiences, and outside media influences.</p>
